Cogta minister Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma and home affairs minister Aaron Motsoaledi will lead a media briefing on the Covid-19 regulations after President Cyril Ramaphosa's address on Monday night. Ramaphosa announced that SA would remain under level 3 of the national lockdown. The president also confirmed that the ban on alcohol sales would continue, and that the curfew had been extended although it would be an hour shorter.